def: An air-filled gap in a magnetic or electric circuit; specif.,in a dynamo or motor, the space between the field-magnet poles andthe armature; clearance.
Relating to acceleration; adding to velocity; quickening. Reid.
Some time ago; formerly. [Scot.] Sir W. Scott.-- a.
To separate chaff from grain.Winnow not with every wind. Ecclus. v. 9.
Conversion into, or formation of, horn; a becoming like horn.
A region or tract of land; esp., the open field; grass country.[South Africa]
A Latin preposition, denoting beyond, outside of; -- often usedin composition as a prefix signifying outside of, beyond, besides, orin addition to what is denoted by the word to which it is prefixed.
The state of being gibbous or gibbose; gibbousness.
A species of apple that ripens very early. Bacon.

A large carnivorous reptile of the Crocodile family, peculiarto America. It has a shorter and broader snout than the crocodile,and the large teeth of the lower jaw shut into pits in the upper jaw,which has no marginal notches. Besides the common species of thesouthern United States, there are allied species in South America.
A subdivision of Carnivora having plantigrade feet. It includesthe bears, raccoons, and allied species.
